{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πόντος</b>, ὁ: <br /> <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>genitive</i> ἐκ ποντόφιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 24.83 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>sea,</b> especially <b>open sea,</b> common from [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus downwards, except in Prose, where it is chiefly used of special seas (see. below 11)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; in the general sense, ὁπότε πνεῦμα ἐκ πόντου εἴη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.26, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 611e, “Ti.” 25a, LXX.Exo.15.5 \">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]; π. ἀπείριτος, ἀπείρων, εὐρύς, μεγακήτης, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.195, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.350, 6.291, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.158; π. ἠεροειδής, ἰοειδής, μέλας, οἶνοψ, 2.263, 11.107, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.79, 23.316; π. ἀτρύγετος, ἰχθυόεις, 15.27, 19.378; opposed to γαῖα, 8.479, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κέλευθοι, πλάξ, πεδίον πόντου, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.195, 1.24, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 150 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. ἁλὸς πολιῆς the <b>wide waters</b> of the grey brine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.59, 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 10, 106 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πόντου γέφυρα, πύλαι, of the Isthmus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 6.39, 10.27. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, π. ἀγαθῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophron Comicus 159; π. χρυσίου 3rd c.BC: Phoenix Iambographus 1.2; ἐκπεσεῖν εἰς τὸν ἀνομοιότητος π. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 273d (cited in 5th-6th c.AD: Damascius Philosophus “de Principiis” 5). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of special seas, π. Ἰκάριος, Γρηΐκιος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.145, 23.230; ὁ Αἰγαῖος π. 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.97, etc.; ὁ π. οὗτος [prev. author] 4.177 (variant)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; Ἰόνιος, Σαρωνικός, Σικελός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 225 (Lyric poetry), “Hipp.” 1200, “Cyc.” 703: especially π. Εὔξεινος, [prev. author] “IT” 125 (Lyric poetry, nisi to be read Ἄξεινος); ὁ Εὔξεινος π. 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.6, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.96, 97 (called Ἄξεινος, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 218 (Lyric poetry))\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; generally called simply ὁ Πόντος or Πόντος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 878 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.147, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 700, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 354a14, +others; but 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus has also ὁ πόντος\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] for <b>the sea,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.99, 177. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> the country [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Pontus” on the 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] shore of the Black Sea, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Μιθριδάτειος” 8, etc.: \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] <i>adjective</i> Ποντικός (which see). <br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> personified as son of Gaia, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 132, 233f (Cogn. with πάτος, which see) \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4195","accentedUnicode":"Πόντος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4193","matchingForm":"Ποντικός","stepTransliteration":"pontikos","gloss":"Pontus","_searchResultRange":"Acts.18.2@Ac